## Commands

```bash
cd backend && pytest            # Backend contract + integration tests (FakeGCPProvider — no cloud calls)
cd frontend && pytest           # Frontend integration tests
cd backend && ruff check .      # Lint backend
cd frontend && ruff check .     # Lint frontend
cd backend && uvicorn src.main:app --reload   # Run backend dev server
cd frontend && streamlit run src/app.py       # Run frontend dev server

# Monitoring stack (Prometheus :9090, Grafana :3000)
docker compose -f docker-compose.monitoring.yml up -d

# Override upload size limit (bytes); 0 = unlimited
LLMOPS_MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES=0 uvicorn src.main:app --reload

# Opt-in manifest validation against a real Kubernetes API server using server-side dry-run.
# Requires a scratch kubeconfig; NEVER creates real resources (dry_run=["All"]).
LLMOPS_K8S_DRYRUN_KUBECONFIG=~/.kube/scratch-config \
  cd backend && pytest tests/dryrun
```

## Code Style

Python 3.11: Follow standard conventions. Ruff for linting.

## Key Design Decisions & Constraints

- **HF_TOKEN injection**: Every deployment (CPU + GPU, public + private + gated) receives the session's `HF_TOKEN` as a transient env var. GKE path: K8s Secret via `vllm_manifest.generate()`. Lightning AI path: `dep.start(env={"HF_TOKEN": ...})`. Token MUST NOT appear in DB columns, API responses, or log lines (SC-005).
- **model_origin**: Determined once at `create_deployment` time by `hf_model_id.split("/")[0] == session.username`. Values: `"uploaded"` or `"public"`. Stored in `deployments.model_origin` (additive migration, default `"public"`). Never updated after creation.
- **Pipeline-tag bypass**: `is_supported_text_generation_model()` checks the HF Hub `pipeline_tag`. If the tag is `"unknown"` (model uploaded without metadata) AND `model_origin == "uploaded"`, the check is bypassed — the user owns the model and knows what they deployed. Third-party models with unknown tags are still rejected.
- **Pre-deploy check timeout**: 10 seconds. Timeout maps to `hf_hub_unreachable` error code with message "HuggingFace Hub is currently unreachable, please retry." — frontend displays this verbatim.
- **deploy_shortcut flow**: `POST /api/upload/start` response includes `deploy_shortcut: str | None` (= `repository_id`). Frontend sets `st.session_state["shortcut_deploy_model"]` on success. "Use Selected Model" in Select tab also sets this key. The Deploy to Cloud tab pops this key on render and pre-populates the repo ID input.
- **No mock-deploy UI**: The legacy `render_deployment_section()` and `mock_deploy` client call are removed from the frontend. The Deploy to Cloud tab contains only the real GKE + Lightning AI path.

## Recent Changes
- 010-prometheus-grafana-monitoring: Per-deployment Prometheus scrape jobs + Grafana dashboards. Proxy metrics (TTFT, throughput, request outcomes) at `GET /metrics`. Metrics API + HMAC-signed Grafana deep links. Streamlit hybrid UX (native charts + Open in Grafana). `deployment_monitoring` table. GPU hardware N/A when series absent. Post-delete UI hides metrics; 7-day operator retention.
- 009-local-model-hf-deploy: Cloud deployment of user-uploaded HF models. Universal HF_TOKEN injection (CPU + GPU). `model_origin` field on deployments. Upload-to-deploy shortcut. "My Upload" badge in Deployments list. Pipeline-tag bypass for user-owned models. Pre-deploy timeout/auth error codes. Upload size raised (10 GB/file Streamlit, 50 GB backend default). Legacy mock-deploy section removed; "Model Repository ID" field (private + gated supported). "Use Selected Model" pre-populates Deploy tab.
- 008-gpu-cpu-deploy: Added GPU/CPU hardware selector for public model deployment. GPU path uses Lightning AI managed cloud (LitServe+vLLM); CPU path unchanged (GKE Autopilot + TGI-CPU). New ⚡ Lightning AI credentials tab. `deployments` table extended with `hardware_type` and `lightning_ai_deployment_id`; GKE columns made nullable.

